column5: This is a little project I built for my folks quite some time ago but never had any pics of it. I took a couple of shots last month when I was back in Ontario. Got a lot of hours into this beast and it was built with no plans and just a rough sketch. It is made of solid pine (except the back. This was 1/4" pine plywood).
Nice! You could put a lot of tackle in there.
Looks solid. I might say your an amazing man Dave.
very nice !  i just made all my ballisters and hand rails for my stairs...
Fine work I must say, looks great!
That's just beautiful Drifter.  Your Folks are very lucky, I'd say.
Very nice piece of work. Great job!
~~~looks great But where's the wine rack??
Behind the doors on the lower right side.
Nice work.  To make it really pop, think about some crown molding around the centre section
